%spark

import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

final val BaseFilePath = "file:///learn"
final val NetflixTitlesRaw = "/netflix/netflix_titles_raw.csv"
final val NetflixTitlesFormatted = "/netflix/netflix_titles.csv"

val netflixData = spark.read
  //.option("mode", "FAILFAST")
  //.option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED")
  .option("header", "true")
  .option("inferSchema", "true")
  .option("encoding", "UTF-8")
  .csv(s"$BaseFilePath/$NetflixTitlesFormatted")

// see the underlying inferredSchema
netflixData.printSchema
val inferredSchema = netflixData.schema
netflixData.createOrReplaceTempView("netflix_raw")
spark.sql("show tables").show

val cleanTypes = netflixData.select("*").where(col("type").isInCollection(Seq("Movie", "TV Show")))

val tvShows = netflixDataStrict.except(intersection)
tvShows.sort(asc("show_id")).show()
